data.name: Label4.Text
data.value:
1. Click “Manage” from the menu bar.
2. If you are looking for a book, select “Book”. Otherwise, “Non-Printed Materials”. Click “Search” to open the search window.
3. In the search box, you may enter the book’s information such as title, author, publisher, book number, etc. or the name of the non-printed material in order to find it.
4. The book or non-printed material will be shown in the box below if it is present in the library.
5. Books and non-printed materials are labeled as “Available” indicating that it is open to be borrowed.

data.name: Label3.Text
data.value:
1. Click “Manage” from the menu bar.
2. Select “Update” from Book or from Non-Printed Materials to open the Update window.
3. You may manually enter the book number or Material Number to search the book or non-printed material that you wanted to update or you may use the barcode scanner for easier and faster searching.
4. Click the search button
5. Update the book or non-printed material’s information and then click the update button to successfully save the changes.

data.name: Label1.Text
data.value:
1. Click “Manage” from the menu bar.
2. Select “Add” from Book or from Non-Printed Materials to open the Add window.
3. Fill out all of the information needed.
4. Click the add button to successfully add and save the book or the non-printed material.
